## 3. North-star-distance trend — reading the column top-to-bottom

This section reads the **north-star distance** column (and the adversarial outcomes that qualify it)
straight down the 15 rows, and states where the trend holds steady toward the frozen north star and
where it trends away. It cites arcs by number. It reports the record; it does not assert the
project's true intent.

### 3.1 The dominant pattern: steady on-vector, with the needle moved only at two points

Reading top to bottom, the column is **overwhelmingly `on-vector`** (arcs 1, 2, 4, 6, 7, 8, 10, 12,
13, 14, 15 — eleven of fifteen), with **two `pivoted`** rows (arcs 5, 11) and **two `advancing`**
rows (arcs 3, 9). The record's own framing is internally consistent: the frozen north star splits
into "the foundation I built" vs "the METHOD I lack," and the great majority of arcs are explicitly
**foundation / instrument-trust / method-discipline work** rather than phenomenon measurement. On
that reading the steady `on-vector` run is the expected shape, not drift — the project spends most of
its energy building and disciplining the instrument the frozen Q5/Q6 demand, and only twice claims to
have moved a frozen-question needle.

The **two `advancing` rows are the only points where the record claims a frozen-question needle
moved**, and both are exactly where the audit's adversarial layer pushed hardest:
- **Arc 3** (advancing on the phenomenon, Obs1/Obs4) — adversarial check found the north-star
  *framing* wrong on a load-bearing point: Task 017b's in-window float32/float64 precision-ratio hit
  is a genuine **Obs7** down-payment that the arc miscalled "banked." The *direction* (advancing,
  not arrived) survives; the "Obs7 untouched in-window" wording does not. Net effect on the trend:
  the phenomenon axis was touched **earlier and more** than Arc 3's own field-3 text admits.
- **Arc 9** (advancing, Q3 answered outright via BACL) — the substantive Q3 closure stands, but the
  **superlative** "first arc to close a frozen open question" does not: the May-13 transfer-law /
  Theorem 3 / Task 017c work (Arc 3-4-5 lineage) already closed Obs7 and answered Q4 per the ledger.
  Net effect: needle-movement is spread across **more arcs** than the two `advancing` labels suggest.

So the trend reading holds **steady on-vector**, and the audit's adversarial layer makes the
needle-movement story *broader, not narrower* — it does not surface drift away from the north star;
it surfaces that progress on the phenomenon (especially **Obs7**, the observation the user singled
out as "the single fact that convinced me there is something real") is **under-credited** in the
arc-by-arc labels.

### 3.2 Where the trend holds steady toward the north star

- **The early run (arcs 1-2)** is foundation-and-honesty: build the typed kernel, then make the
  AlphaProbe refuse to over-claim. On-vector by construction (the frozen text calls this the
  foundation), adversarially clean.
- **The phenomenon-contact run (arcs 3-5)** turns the honest instrument onto Will's actual GR/SR
  two-form pair, recovers the route-matters phenomenon (Obs1/Obs4) and a partial Obs7, and ends with
  the **curvature pivot** (arc 5) that restates the frozen Q1/Q5 framing almost word-for-word
  ("curvature is the object; the arithmetic signature is the shadow"). The pivot is on the frozen
  axis, not a departure from it.
- **The instrument-trust run (arcs 6-8)** is Q5/Q6 discipline: 15 honest "no"s to a doubled-comb
  finer instrument (arc 6), the dual-arm "is ARM-N reading new data" reframe with a highest-grade
  self-downgrade (arc 7), and the workshop/Vera cross-validation discipline (arc 8). All on-vector at
  the method/trust level.
- **The substrate-derivation run (arcs 9-11)** is the deepest contact with the frozen questions: Q3
  answered from IEEE 754 (arc 9), a disciplined Gate-3 HALT that engages Q5 in the negative (arc 10),
  and the most literal attempt yet at the OBJECT via curvature/K_G (arc 11), which corrects its own
  instrument-object entanglement and restarts. On-vector throughout; the K_G/MCG framing is the most
  V3-shaped the project gets, but the record holds V3 isolation and refuses to promote the imported
  Path-B K_G as a substrate result.
- **The consolidation-and-construction run (arcs 12-15)** returns to building: Vera extraction
  (arc 12), the return to L1 primitive construction (arc 13), the substrate-layer audit (arc 14),
  and the first genuine substrate-construction transplant since the May-11 buildout (arc 15,
  typed_ulp — the substrate's first-class hold on the arithmetic noise floor Q6 names). On-vector at
  the foundation level; the Arc-13/14 "deferral risk" watch did **not** materialize — the map became
  motion within a day.

### 3.3 Where the trend trends away (watches, not divergences)

No arc is classified as diverging from the frozen north star, and the adversarial layer did not
promote any watch to a divergence. The trend reading does surface **three recurring directional
tensions** that the arc reports log as field-4 trajectory-watches (medium confidence, forward reads
of organizing intent — not executed actions, not north-star distance):

1. **Arithmetic-organized momentum vs the curvature pivot (arcs 6, 7, 8, 9, partially 10).** Arc 5's
   curvature-pivot handoff named the arithmetic/route/arm axis for replacement, yet arcs 6-9 continue
   along it (route enumeration, dual-arm, BACL/binade/ulp lattice). Each report flags this as
   instrument-momentum, not divergence, and the record shows it feeding forward: the offset guard,
   the hardened probe, and BACL all carry into later arcs, and arcs 10-11 turn the program back
   toward curvature/Q1. The trend here trends *sideways relative to the pivot* while staying *toward
   the frozen questions* — the frozen north star is the Q1-Q6 set, which is itself arithmetic-path /
   residual-structure framed, so continuing that axis is on-vector to the frozen reference even where
   it runs counter to a later proposed method.
2. **V3-shaped scaffolding (arcs 10-11).** The R=M+C+G / master-invariant / K_G framing is the most
   V3-analogue the project adopts. The record contains it: V3 isolation held, the V3-equivalence is
   carried as contrast not import, and the flagship G/K_G probe is either HALTed (arc 10) or kept
   eval-layer-only with the goal held open (arc 11). The watch is real (energy spent building a
   V3-analogue scaffold) but the discipline held.
3. **Deferral, not divergence (arcs 12-14).** Large designed-but-unrun backlogs (Vera Track A/B,
   tasks 037-040, the 12 transplants). The forward risk on these days is *deferral* — consolidating
   and re-scoping more than measuring. Consistent with a project whose north star is a trustworthy
   METHOD; arc 15 shows the deferral risk did not stick (typed_ulp executed within a day of the
   arc-14 map). The one adversarial *deliver* weakening (arc 13, AC8(d) relaxed post-hoc) lives in
   this run and is a pre-registration-discipline slip on a predicted joint pattern, not a north-star
   drift — the north-star call for arc 13 stands.

### 3.4 Net trend statement

Read top-to-bottom, the north-star-distance column **holds steady on-vector** across all 15 arcs,
with needle-movement claimed at arcs 3 and 9 and method-pivots at arcs 5 and 11. The record shows
**no arc diverging from the frozen north star**; the only directional tensions are
trajectory-watches (arithmetic-momentum-vs-pivot, V3-shaped scaffolding, deferral) that each report
contains and the adversarial layer declined to escalate. The adversarial layer's net effect on the
trend is to **broaden the needle-movement story** (Obs7 touched earlier than Arc 3 admits per the
017b finding; frozen-question closure spread across more arcs than the Arc-9 superlative implies) and
to flag **one pre-registration-discipline slip** (Arc 13 AC8(d)) — neither of which moves any arc off
the on-vector trend. Where the record diverges from a *later proposed method* (the curvature pivot of
arc 5), that is a project-internal organizing-principle question, not distance from the FROZEN north
star, which is the Q1-Q6 / Obs1-7 reference fixed at the top of this file.

